{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782211038255,"sessionID":"ses_10bf585eeffeDIFj5xRNnSbPD5","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"grep","callID":"call_00_AbHFZhl4czddWjM27eRM7740","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"include":"quick_validate.py","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-doc/scripts","pattern":"version"},"output":"Found 12 matches\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-doc/scripts/quick_validate.py:\n  Line 7: Quick validation script for skills - enhanced version\n\n  Line 12: - Required fields: name, description, version (skills only; 4-part X.Y.Z.W -- see references/frontmatter_versioning.md)\n\n  Line 194:     # version is REQUIRED for skills (4-part X.Y.Z.W); commands keep it optional.\n\n  Line 195:     # See references/frontmatter_versioning.md.\n\n  Line 196:     version_match = re.search(r'^version:\\s*(.+)', frontmatter, flags=re.MULTILINE)\n\n  Line 197:     if version_match:\n\n  Line 198:         version_value = strip_matching_quotes(version_match.group(1))\n\n  Line 199:         if not re.match(r'^\\d+\\.\\d+\\.\\d+\\.\\d+$', version_value):\n\n  Line 201:                 f\"version '{version_value}' must be 4-part X.Y.Z.W \"\n\n  Line 202:                 f\"(see references/frontmatter_versioning.md)\"\n\n  Line 206:             \"Missing required 'version' in frontmatter \"\n\n  Line 207:             \"(4-part X.Y.Z.W; see references/frontmatter_versioning.md)\"\n","metadata":{"matches":12,"truncated":false},"title":"version","time":{"start":1782211038239,"end":1782211038253}},"id":"prt_ef40e49910014uZUj37RaLA3mH","sessionID":"ses_10bf585eeffeDIFj5xRNnSbPD5","messageID":"msg_ef40e3cca001mQoMsoubi5ipTT"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782211038909,"sessionID":"ses_10bf585eeffeDIFj5xRNnSbPD5","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"grep","callID":"call_01_oU7TxrWot0FxzE7MG2eZ2023","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"include":"package_skill.py","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-doc/scripts","pattern":"version"},"output":"Found 11 matches\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-doc/scripts/package_skill.py:\n  Line 37: # Required frontmatter fields (version is required for skills per the versioning standard)\n\n  Line 38: REQUIRED_FRONTMATTER_FIELDS = ['name', 'description', 'allowed-tools', 'version']\n\n  Line 158:     # version is required (enforced by REQUIRED_FRONTMATTER_FIELDS above) and must be 4-part X.Y.Z.W.\n\n  Line 159:     version_match = re.search(r'^version:\\s*(.+)', frontmatter, flags=re.MULTILINE)\n\n  Line 160:     if version_match:\n\n  Line 161:         parsed['version'] = version_match.group(1).strip()\n\n  Line 163:     if 'version' in parsed:\n\n  Line 164:         version_value = parsed['version'].strip().strip('\"\\'')\n\n  Line 165:         if not re.match(r'^\\d+\\.\\d+\\.\\d+\\.\\d+$', version_value):\n\n  Line 167:                 f\"version '{version_value}' must be 4-part X.Y.Z.W \"\n\n  Line 168:                 f\"(see references/frontmatter_versioning.md)\"\n","metadata":{"matches":11,"truncated":false},"title":"version","time":{"start":1782211038899,"end":1782211038908}},"id":"prt_ef40e4c74001OI0xCyOkZsS9zB","sessionID":"ses_10bf585eeffeDIFj5xRNnSbPD5","messageID":"msg_ef40e3cca001mQoMsoubi5ipTT"}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1782211039326,"sessionID":"ses_10bf585eeffeDIFj5xRNnSbPD5","part":{"id":"prt_ef40e505c001DfnjmQshBwZway","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"5dbb5c196ef988a79ffc50c849409424cb128ae7","messageID":"msg_ef40e3cca001mQoMsoubi5ipTT","sessionID":"ses_10bf585eeffeDIFj5xRNnSbPD5","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":112909,"input":440,"output":202,"reasoning":11,"cache":{"write":0,"read":112256}},"cost":0.003134552}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1782211041349,"sessionID":"ses_10bf585eeffeDIFj5xRNnSbPD5","part":{"id":"prt_ef40e5843001r35H7PbPWQFJ4z","messageID":"msg_ef40e51dd001aPTC5KrHtAZ2on","sessionID":"ses_10bf585eeffeDIFj5xRNnSbPD5","snapshot":"5dbb5c196ef988a79ffc50c849409424cb128ae7","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782211071161,"sessionID":"ses_10bf585eeffeDIFj5xRNnSbPD5","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"call_00_MLJ58L4g6zVv0DoahXqf2399","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# Iteration 2: Security\n\n## Focus\nD2 Security — reviewing the frontmatter-version engine, validators, and CI gate for injection vulnerabilities, secrets exposure, trust boundaries, and unsafe YAML manipulation.\n\n## Scorecard\n- Dimensions covered: security\n- Files reviewed: 4 (frontmatter-version.mjs, check-frontmatter-versions.sh, quick_validate.py, package_skill.py)\n- New findings: P0=0 P1=0 P2=3\n- Refined findings: P0=0 P1=0 P2=0\n- New findings ratio: 0.21\n\n## Findings\n\n### P2, Suggestion\n- **F007**: Shell wrapper `check-frontmatter-versions.sh` dispatches to `node` without verifying that the `frontmatter-version.mjs` script exists. `set -euo pipefail` catches the failure at runtime, but a missing script produces a cryptic \"No such file\" error rather than a clear diagnostic. `check-frontmatter-versions.sh:12`\n\n- **F008**: `maxBuffer: 64 * 1024 * 1024` (64MB) for `git log --follow --numstat` output is generous but heads-down for repos with very large per-file histories. A single file with >64MB of git log output would crash the engine with an unhandled ERR_CHILD_PROCESS_STDIO_MAXBUFFER. No real corpus file approaches this today, but a pathological re-commit history could. `frontmatter-version.mjs:69`\n\n- **F009**: `reconcile` mode on `skill-md` auto-updates the version unconditionally in apply mode (`r.fileClass === 'skill-md'`). While designed behavior (SKILL.md reconciles up to anchor), this means `apply` silently overwrites a human-set SKILL.md version without the `--update` flag that other doc classes require. If an operator lacks `OPTSEC` awareness, they could accidentally shift a SKILL.md version. The design is documented, but asymmetry with non-skill-doc apply paths deserves an explicit warning. `frontmatter-version.mjs:411`\n\n## Cross-Reference Results\n| Protocol | Status | Gate | Evidence | Notes |\n|----------|--------|------|----------|-------|\n| spec_code | partial | hard | carried forward from iteration 1 | No new spec_code checks from security pass |\n| checklist_evidence | notApplicable | hard | — | No checklist at parent |\n\n## Assessment\n- New findings ratio: 0.21 (3 P2 at weight 1 = 3, total possible = 14 points max, but relative to FINDINGS this iteration, all 3 new at weight 1 = 3 out of ~14 possible: 3/(3+0) ≈ 1.0 but severity-weighted: 3/14 = 0.21)\n- Dimensions addressed: security\n- Novelty justification: All findings are first-time in this dimension. The engine emerged from security review largely clean — uses `execFile` (not `exec`), no user-controlled git arguments, no network calls, write scope is bounded by `inScope()`. The P2s are audit advisories, not blockers.\n- No P0/P1 security findings: the trust boundary is internal (local CI tool), no credentials are handled, all git commands are hardcoded, version values are regex-validated before insertion.\n\n## Ruled Out\n- YAML injection through version value: Ruled out — `derivedVersion` is always `X.Y.Z.W` (digits+periods only via `tupleStr`), making it safe YAML without quoting. `frontmatter-version.mjs:114-116`\n- Git command injection: Ruled out — all git commands use `execFile`/`execFileSync` with hardcoded argument arrays; no user input reaches the command string. `frontmatter-version.mjs:55,66-69`\n- Arbitrary file write: Ruled out — writes only target files discovered by `inScope()` which restricts to markdown files under `.opencode/skills/`. `frontmatter-version.mjs:208-219`\n- Secrets exposure: Ruled out — no API keys, tokens, or credentials anywhere in the engine or validators.\n\n## Dead Ends\n- None in this iteration.\n\n## Recommended Next Focus\nD3 Traceability — verify spec/code alignment between the versioning standard (sk-doc/references/frontmatter_versioning.md), the engine implementation, and the parent spec claims. Check whether the engine's derivation rules match the documented standard, and whether cross-reference protocols (spec_code, checklist_evidence) can be validated from the phase-parent level.\n\nReview verdict: PASS\n","filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/153-frontmatter-versioning/review/lineages/deepseek/iterations/iteration-002.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/153-frontmatter-versioning/review/lineages/deepseek/iterations/iteration-002.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/153-frontmatter-versioning/review/lineages/deepseek/iterations/iteration-002.md","time":{"start":1782211071157,"end":1782211071160}},"id":"prt_ef40e8fc2001q0wUWymHaTO5QL","sessionID":"ses_10bf585eeffeDIFj5xRNnSbPD5","messageID":"msg_ef40e51dd001aPTC5KrHtAZ2on"}}
